{"code": "def make_point_class():\n    def __init__(self, x, y):\n        self['set']('x', x)\n        self['set']('y', y)\n\n    def move(self, dx, dy):\n        self['set']('x', self['get']('x') + dx)\n        self['set']('y', self['get']('y') + dy)\n        return (self['get']('x'), self['get']('y'))\n\n    def coords(self):\n        return (self['get']('x'), self['get']('y'))\n\n    return make_class(locals())\n\nPoint = make_point_class()\n\np = Point['new'](1, 2)\nfrozen = freeze(p)\nassert frozen['get']('coords')() == (1, 2)     # reads still work through the wrapper\nassert frozen['set']('x', 99) == 'frozen'      # writes are refused\nassert frozen['get']('x') == 1                 # the value never changed\nassert p['get']('x') == 1                      # the underlying instance is safe\nassert p['get']('move')(3, 4) == (4, 6)        # the raw instance is still mutable\nassert frozen['get']('coords')() == (4, 6)     # the wrapper reflects raw changes", "trace": [{"line": 1, "event": "step_line", "func_name": "<module>", "globals": {}, "ordered_globals": [], "stack_to_render": [], "heap": {}, "stdout": ""}, {"line": 16, "event": "step_line", "func_name": "<module>", "globals": {"make_point_class": ["REF", 1]}, "ordered_globals": ["make_point_class"], "stack_to_render": [], "heap": {"1": ["FUNCTION", "make_point_class()", null]}, "stdout": ""}, {"line": 1, "event": "call", "func_name": "make_point_class", "globals": {"make_point_class": ["REF", 1]}, "ordered_globals": ["make_point_class"], "stack_to_render": [{"func_name": "make_point_class", "is_parent": false, "frame_id": 1, "parent_frame_id_list": [], "encoded_locals": {}, "ordered_varnames": [], "is_zombie": false, "is_highlighted": true, "unique_hash": "make_point_class_f1"}], "heap": {"1": ["FUNCTION", "make_point_class()", null]}, "stdout": ""}, {"line": 2, "event": "step_line", "func_name": "make_point_class", "globals": {"make_point_class": ["REF", 1]}, "ordered_globals": ["make_point_class"], "stack_